<br>
<br>
<br><font size=3D2 face=3D"sans-serif">In addition to the draft symposium p=
roceedings,
we intend to continue the TFP tradition of &nbsp;</font>
<br><font size=3D2 face=3D"sans-serif">publishing a high-quality subset of
contributions in the Intellect series on Trends in &nbsp;</font><font size=
=3D3>
&nbsp; &nbsp;</font>
<br><font size=3D2 face=3D"sans-serif">Functional Programming. All TFP auth=
ors
will be invited to submit revised papers after the &nbsp;</font>
<br><font size=3D2 face=3D"sans-serif">symposium. These will be refereed us=
ing
normal conference standards and a subset of the best &nbsp;</font><font siz=
e=3D3>
&nbsp; &nbsp;</font>
<br><font size=3D2 face=3D"sans-serif">papers, over all categories, will be
selected for publication. Papers will be judged on their &nbsp;</font><font=
 size=3D3>
&nbsp;</font>
<br><font size=3D2 face=3D"sans-serif">contribution to the research area wi=
th
appropriate criteria applied to each category of paper. </font><font size=
=3D3>&nbsp;
&nbsp;</font>
<br>
<br><font size=3D2 face=3D"sans-serif">Student papers will be given extra f=
eedback
by the Program Committee in order to assist those &nbsp;</font><font size=
=3D3>
&nbsp;</font>
<br><font size=3D2 face=3D"sans-serif">unfamiliar with the publication proc=
ess.
